Key Match Events: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 29 points in 29 minutes
Chet Holmgren matched Shai Gilgeous-Alexander's point total
The Thunder scored 75 points in the first half, its season-high for points in a half
The Thunder made 14 free throws on 15 attempts in the first half
The Rockets had 16 turnovers, the fewest turnovers OKC has forced in a game this season
Pre-Game Insights: Experts predicted the Thunder to win based on their recent performance
Post-Match Reflections: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander expressed pride in his team's effort after the win
Chet Holmgren noted that former Thunder player Steven Adams'moves you super gently and there's nothing you can do about it'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Thunder entered the game 21st in the league in offensive rating, but ended up with the league's 16th best offensive rating
The Rockets' Alperen Sengun had his worst game against the Thunder, with 11 points on 3-for-12 shooting
The Thunder's defense lived up to its suffocating standards, even if its turnover count didn't
Others: The game was played at the Paycom Center in Oklahoma City
The Thunder's next game is against the Golden State Warriors on November 10
